A well known Nigerian politician, Joe Igbokwe who was the spokesperson of All Progressive Congress, APC, has taken to his official Facebook page to reveal that more desperate destruction and wanton killings will still come as long as the 2023 Presidential election is concerned.
While sharing on his official Facebook page, the exceptionally boisterous APC supporter, and special adviser to the Lagos State governor, Babajide Sanwo-Olu, on drainage and water resources, Joe Igbokwe made it known that more desperate destruction and wanton killings will still come, and this is because of the 2023 Presidential election, adding that those behind these acts are afraid of tomorrow.
Further speaking, the outstanding politician, Joe Igbokwe, he stated that their act is like the last kicks of a dying horse.
According to his words, Joe Igbokwe said, “Know this and have Inner peace, more desperate destruction and wanton killings will still come. It is all about 2023. These criminals are afraid of tomorrow. This is the last kicks of a dying horse”.
